SENATE BILL DRS45532-NHa-186
Short Title: Allergy Safe Schools Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Senator Chitlik (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO INCREASE FOOD ALLERGY SAFETY IN PUBLIC SCHOOLS BY
3 REQUIRING A NURSE IN EVERY SCHOOL, REQUIRING SCHOOL STAFF TO
4 ATTEND TRAINING ON RECOGNIZING AND TREATING ANAPHYLAXIS,
5 REQUIRING MEDICAL ACTION PLANS FOR STUDENTS WITH FOOD ALLERGIES,
6 AND PROHIBITING FOOD AT SCHOOL CELEBRATIONS.
7 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
8
9 PART I. A NURSE IN EVERY SCHOOL
10 SECTION 1.(a) G.S. 115C-47 is amended by adding a new subdivision to read:
11 "(73) To Provide at Least One School Nurse in Every School. – Local boards of
12 education shall ensure that each school within the local school administrative
13 unit is staffed by at least one full-time, permanent school nurse."
14 SECTION 1.(b) G.S. 115C-150.12C is amended by adding a new subdivision to
15 read:
16 "(39) To provide at least one school nurse in every school. – The board of trustees
17 shall ensure that each school is staffed by at least one full-time, permanent
18 school nurse."
19 SECTION 1.(c) G.S. 115C-218.75 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
20 "(p) At Least One School Nurse. – A charter school shall ensure that the school is staffed
21 by at least one full-time, permanent school nurse."
22 SECTION 1.(d) G.S. 115C-238.66 is amended by adding a new subdivision to read:
23 "(23) At least one school nurse required. – A regional school shall ensure that the
24 school is staffed by at least one full-time, permanent school nurse."
25 SECTION 1.(e) G.S. 116-239.8(b) is amended by adding a new subdivision to read:
26 "(26) At least one school nurse required. – A laboratory school shall ensure that the
27 school is staffed by at least one full-time, permanent school nurse."
28 SECTION 1.(f) There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
29 Public Instruction the sum of ninety-two million dollars ($92,000,000) in recurring funds
30 beginning with the 2026-2027 fiscal year to increase the School Health Personnel Allotment.
31 These funds shall be used to increase positions for school nurses in order to provide at least one
32 full-time, permanent school nurse in every school in a public school unit.
33 SECTION 1.(g) Funds provided pursuant to this act shall supplement and not
34 supplant any funds from any source already provided for school nurses.
35 SECTION 1.(h) This section is effective July 1, 2026, and applies beginning with
36 the 2026-2027 school year.
